kěnéng zài nǐde shēnghuó zhōng nǐ yòngbudào
可能在你的生活中你用不到
You might not use in your daily life.

00:12:57.000 --> 00:12:57.966
zhèyàngde értóng dúwù
这样的儿童读物
This kind of children's book.

00:12:58.000 --> 00:12:59.800
wǒ jiù bú jiànyì nǐmen qù kàn
我就不建议你们去看
I wouldn't recommend you to read.

00:12:59.833 --> 00:13:01.600
bú jiànyì nǐmen qù yòngtā xuéxí le
不建议你们去用它学习了
I wouldn't recommend using it for learning.

00:13:01.600 --> 00:13:02.533
èn méicuò
嗯 没错
Um, exactly.

00:13:02.533 --> 00:13:05.633
yīnwèi yǒuyìxiē értóng dúwù quèshí yǒu yìxiē huà ba
因为有一些儿童读物确实有一些话吧
Because in some children's books, there are indeed some expressions.

00:13:05.633 --> 00:13:07.000
tā bútài chángyòng
他不太常用
That are not very common.

00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:08.866
érqiě hěn... zěnme shuōne
而且很...怎么说呢
And very... how should I put it?

00:13:08.866 --> 00:13:11.800
hěn kě'ài... shìhé xiǎoháizi shuōchūkǒu
很可爱...适合小孩子说出口
Very cute... suitable for children to say.

00:13:11.833 --> 00:13:13.666
nà rúguǒ wǒmen dàrén shuōchūkǒu ne
那如果我们大人说出口呢
But what if we adults say them?

00:13:13.666 --> 00:13:16.433
jiù gǎnjué hǎoxiàng tài kě'ài le
就感觉好像太可爱了
It just feels like it's too "cute."

00:13:16.433 --> 00:13:18.433
duì jiù bǐrúshuō chīmiàn
对 就比如说吃面
Right, like for example, eating noodles.

00:13:18.433 --> 00:13:19.200
tāmen kěnéng huì shuō
他们可能会说
They might say.

00:13:19.200 --> 00:13:20.000
chī miànmian
吃面面
"Eat noodle-noodle."

00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:21.000
duì miànmian
对 面面
Right, "noodle-noodle."

00:13:21.033 --> 00:13:23.066
ránhòu nàge dōngdong (dōngxi)
然后那个东东（东西）
And then that "dong-dong" (thing).

00:13:23.066 --> 00:13:25.066
dōngdong hǎo qíguài
东东 好奇怪
"Dong-dong" is so weird.

00:13:25.100 --> 00:13:25.866
nà zhèyàng de huà
那这样的话
Then in that case.

00:13:25.866 --> 00:13:27.333
nǐ jiù bùnéng wánquán zhàozhe shuō le
你就不能完全照着说了
You can't follow it exactly.

00:13:27.333 --> 00:13:28.766
yàoburán tāmen kěnéng huì juéde
要不然他们可能会觉得
Otherwise, they might think.

00:13:28.766 --> 00:13:30.266
nǐshì yíge hěn qíguài de rén
你是一个很奇怪的人
You are a very strange person.

00:13:30.300 --> 00:13:30.400
duì
对
Right.

00:13:30.400 --> 00:13:31.633
duìduì
对对
Right, right.

00:13:31.633 --> 00:13:34.600
nǐ juéde zhǐyào huì shuō hànyǔ
你觉得只要会说汉语
Do you think as long as someone can speak Chinese.

00:13:34.733 --> 00:13:36.466
nǐ jiù huì jiāo hànyǔ ma
你就会教汉语吗
They will be able to teach Chinese?

00:13:36.600 --> 00:13:38.000
wǒ juéde búshì de
我觉得不是的
I don't think so.

00:13:38.066 --> 00:13:41.100
yīnwèi wǒ měiyíge jíbié de xuésheng
因为我每一个级别的学生
Because for students of every level.

00:13:41.100 --> 00:13:43.666
tā shì yào zhēnduìxìng de yìxiē fāngfǎ
他是要针对性的一些方法
Specific methods are required.

00:13:43.666 --> 00:13:45.866
lái jiāo tāmen de
来教他们的
To teach them.

00:13:45.866 --> 00:13:49.200
nà rúguǒ shì yíge zhǐ huì shuō zhōngwén de zhōngguórén
那如果是一个只会说中文的中国人
If it is a Chinese person who only knows how to speak Chinese.

00:13:49.200 --> 00:13:51.833
tā bù dǒngde zhège jiāode bànfǎ
他不懂得这个教的办法
But doesn't understand the methods of teaching.

00:13:51.833 --> 00:13:52.666
tā zhǐshì shuō
他只是说
And they just say.

00:13:52.666 --> 00:13:55.833
wǒ shuō yíjù hànyǔ nǐ jiù néng xué jiùxíngle
我说一句汉语你就能学就行了
"I'll say a sentence in Chinese and you just learn it."

00:13:55.833 --> 00:13:57.666
qíshí zhège shì bùkěyǐ de
其实这个是不可以的
Actually, that doesn't work.

00:13:57.666 --> 00:14:01.433
ránhòu wǒ juéde shìhuì "shìdéqífǎn"
然后我觉得是会"适得其反"
And I think it will be "counterproductive."

00:14:01.500 --> 00:14:03.300
búdàn méiyǒu jiāohǎo
不但没有教好
Not only will they not teach well.

00:14:03.300 --> 00:14:05.733
fǎn'ér tāde nǎozili yǒu hǎoduō hǎoduō cí
反而他的脑子里有好多好多词
But instead, the student's head will be full of words.

00:14:05.733 --> 00:14:09.800
dànshì shuōchūkǒu hěnduō zhōngguórén yě tīngbumíngbai
但是说出来很多中国人也听不明白
But when they speak, many Chinese people still won't understand.

00:14:09.866 --> 00:14:10.866
duì èn
对 嗯
Right, um.

00:14:10.966 --> 00:14:13.066
qíshí jiù bǐrúshuō
其实就比如说
Actually, for example.

00:14:13.133 --> 00:14:15.933
zhōngguórén zhīdào hěnduō yīngyǔ de yǔfǎ
中国人知道很多英语的语法
Chinese people know a lot of English grammar.

00:14:15.933 --> 00:14:16.666
dànshì ne
但是呢
But.

00:14:16.666 --> 00:14:17.933
yīngyǔ de mǔyǔzhě
英语的母语者
Native English speakers.

00:14:17.933 --> 00:14:20.766
tāmen kěnéng bù zhīdào yǒu zhèxiē yǔfǎ
他们可能不知道有这些语法
Might not know these grammar rules exist.

00:14:20.766 --> 00:14:23.033
nà hànyǔ yěshì yíyàng de
那汉语也是一样的
Chinese is the same.

00:14:23.066 --> 00:14:24.800
yīnwèi wǒmen shì zhuānyè de lǎoshī
因为我们是专业的老师
Because we are professional teachers.

00:14:24.833 --> 00:14:27.266
wǒmen zhīdào hànyǔ li yǒu hěn duō yǔfǎ
我们知道汉语里有很多语法
We know there is a lot of grammar in Chinese.

00:14:27.266 --> 00:14:30.666
dànshì ne biéde zhōngguórén tāmen shì bù zhīdào de
但是呢 别的中国人他们是不知道的
But other Chinese people don't know about them.

00:14:30.666 --> 00:14:33.000
bǐrúshuō wǒ jǔ yíge hěn jiǎndān de lìzi
比如说我举一个很简单的例子
For instance, let me give a very simple example.

00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:36.200
"tā jiéhūnle" hé "tā jiéguohūn"
"他结婚了"和"他结过婚"
"He got married" and "He has been married before."

00:14:36.200 --> 00:14:37.966
zhèshì wánquán bùtóng de yìsi
这是完全不同的意思
These have completely different meanings.

00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:39.833
duì zhège "le" hé "guò"
对 这个"了"和"过"
Right, "le" and "guo."

00:14:39.833 --> 00:14:41.200
dōushì guòqùshì
 都是过去式
Both are past tenses.

00:14:41.233 --> 00:14:43.233
dànshì shì yìsi wánquán bùtóng
但是是意思完全不同
But the meanings are totally different.

00:14:43.233 --> 00:14:44.400
duì nà zhōngguórén ne
对 那中国人呢
Right, as for Chinese people.

00:14:44.400 --> 00:14:47.300
tā k\u1ebndìng zhīdào tāmen de yìsi shì bùtóng de
他肯定知道他们的意思是不同的
They certainly know the meanings are different.

00:14:47.300 --> 00:14:49.300
k\u1ebshìne tāmen (mǔyǔzhě) búhuì zhùyì dào
可是呢 他们（母语者）不会注意到
But they (native speakers) won't notice.

00:14:49.300 --> 00:14:51.666
tāmen yě bùzhīdào zěnme qù gěinǐ jiěshì
他们也不知道怎么去给你解释
And they don't know how to explain it to you.

00:14:51.666 --> 00:14:53.200
tāmen de qūbié shì shénme
他们的区别是什么
What the difference between them is.

00:14:53.200 --> 00:14:55.066
bǐrúshuō hěnduō zhōngguórén huì gàosu nǐ
比如说很多中国人会告诉你
For example, many Chinese people will tell you.

00:14:55.100 --> 00:14:56.533
nǐ jiā "le" jiù duì le
你加"了"就对了
"Just add 'le' and it's correct."

00:14:56.533 --> 00:14:58.300
jiā "le" jiùshì guòqùshì
加"了"就是过去式
"Adding 'le' makes it past tense."

00:14:58.300 --> 00:15:00.266
dànshì wǒmen yǒu "yào...le"
但是我们有 "要...了"
But we have "yao... le" (about to).

00:15:00.300 --> 00:15:02.466
bǐrúshuō "wǒ yào qù lǚxíng le"
比如说"我要去旅行了"
Like "I'm about to go traveling."

00:15:02.466 --> 00:15:04.733
nà zhège shìqing méiyǒu fāshēng ne
那这个事情没有发生呢
In that case, the event hasn't happened yet.

00:15:04.733 --> 00:15:05.966
duì shìde
对是的
Right, exactly.

00:15:06.000 --> 00:15:08.333
ránhòu ne wǒ hái yùdào guo zhèyàng de qíngkuàng
然后呢我还遇到过这样的情况
And I've also encountered situations like this.

00:15:08.333 --> 00:15:10.000
jiùshì yìxiē lǎoshī
就是一些老师
Where some teachers.

00:15:10.000 --> 00:15:14.466
tāmen huì yìzhí yìzhí qù jiūzhèng xuésheng de fāyīn
他们会一直一直去纠正学生的发音
They keep correcting students' pronunciation constantly.

00:15:14.566 --> 00:15:16.633
tāmen juéde fāyīn zhǔn le
他们觉得发音准了
They think if the pronunciation is accurate.

00:15:16.666 --> 00:15:18.300
zhège rén de hànyǔ jiù hǎo le
这个人的汉语就好了
Then the person's Chinese will be good.

00:15:18.300 --> 00:15:20.333
nǐ juéde zhège fāngfǎ duì ma
你觉得这个方法对吗
Do you think this method is correct?

00:15:20.333 --> 00:15:23.633
shǒuxiān wǒ juéde shuō fāyīn zhǔnquè (hànyǔ hǎo)
首先我觉得说发音准确（汉语好）
First of all, I think saying "accurate pronunciation equals good Chinese."

00:15:23.633 --> 00:15:24.833
zhège shì duìde
这个是对的
Is correct in a way.

00:15:24.866 --> 00:15:26.800
dànshì rúguǒ tā yǐjīng xué le hǎo jiǔ
但是如果他已经学了好久
But if they have already studied for a long time.

00:15:26.800 --> 00:15:28.600
ránhòu yìzhí jiūyīn dehuà
然后一直纠音的话
And you keep correcting their tones.

00:15:28.600 --> 00:15:32.000
zhè jiàn shìqing shì duì xuésheng dǎjī hěn yánzhòng de
这件事情是对学生打击很严重的
This can be a very serious blow to the student's confidence.

00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:34.200
wǒmen zài jiǎng jiāo chūjí xuésheng de shíhou
我们在讲教初级学生的时候
When we talk about teaching beginner students.

00:15:34.200 --> 00:15:35.466
wǒmen zuòwéi hànyǔ lǎoshī
我们作为汉语老师
As Chinese teachers.

00:15:35.466 --> 00:15:37.266
wǒmen yīnggāi bǎ pīnyīn jiāohǎo
我们应该把拼音教好
We should teach Pinyin well.

00:15:37.266 --> 00:15:40.900
zhège jīchǔ yīnggāi gěi tā dǎ hǎo
这个基础应该给他打好
A good foundation should be laid for them.

00:15:40.900 --> 00:15:42.833
ràng tāde nàge fāyīn hǎo yìdiǎn
让他的那个发音好一点
To make their pronunciation better.

00:15:42.900 --> 00:15:44.833
dāng tā yǐjīng hěn gāo jíbié le
当他已经很高级别了
When they are already at an advanced level.

00:15:44.833 --> 00:15:46.600
tāde fāyīn yǒuwèntí le
他的发音有问题了
If there's an issue with their pronunciation.

00:15:46.633 --> 00:15:48.866
nǐ yàoshì chángcháng jiūyīn dehuà
你要是常常纠音的话
If you correct their pronunciation constantly.

00:15:48.866 --> 00:15:50.200
tā huì méi zìxìn
他会没自信
They will lose confidence.

00:15:50.200 --> 00:15:50.833
shìde
是的
Yes.

00:15:50.866 --> 00:15:54.666
érqiě tā huì juéde zhèshì yìmén hěn kūzào de yǔyán
而且他会觉得这是一门很枯燥的语言
Moreover, they will feel that this is a very dull language.

00:15:54.666 --> 00:15:57.000
duì zhèyàng de huà tā k\u1ebngnéng jiùhuì fàngqì
对 这样的话他可能就会放弃
Right, and then they might just give up.

00:15:57.000 --> 00:15:58.800
tā juéde fāyīn tài nán le
他觉得发音太难了
They'll feel that pronunciation is too difficult.

00:15:58.800 --> 00:16:00.333
ránhòu wèishénme wǒ shuōde měiyíjù huà
然后为什么我说的每一句话
"And why is every sentence I say..."

00:16:00.333 --> 00:16:01.900
nǐ dōu yào jiūzhèng wǒ ne
你都要纠正我呢
"...you have to correct me every time."

00:16:01.900 --> 00:16:03.466
wǒ juéde bù yǐngxiǎng dàyì
我觉得不影响大意
I feel that if it doesn't affect the general meaning.

00:16:03.466 --> 00:16:05.666
bù yǐngxiǎng zhěnggè de yìsi de shíhou
不影响整个的意思的时候
When it doesn't affect the overall meaning.

00:16:05.666 --> 00:16:07.133
bù xūyào qù jiūzhèng tā
不需要去纠正他
There's no need to correct them.

00:16:07.133 --> 00:16:10.466
dāng tā yǒuyíge cí zhēnde wánquán yìsi bù yíyàng le
当他有一个词真的完全意思不一样了
When they use a word that makes the meaning completely different.

00:16:10.466 --> 00:16:12.466
jiùshì tīngqǐlái wánquán bùyíyàng le
就是听起来完全不一样了
I mean, when it sounds like something else entirely.

00:16:12.466 --> 00:16:14.600
wǒ juéde nǐ kěyǐ gēntā shuō yíxià
我觉得你可以跟他说一下
I think you can mention it to them.

00:16:14.600 --> 00:16:17.066
ránhòu mànmande tā kěnéng huì zìjǐ yě zhīdào
然后慢慢的他可能会自己也知道
Then gradually, they might realize it themselves.

00:16:17.066 --> 00:16:18.600
yìdiǎn yìdiǎn de gǎiguòlái
一点一点的改过来
And fix it bit by bit.

00:16:18.600 --> 00:16:20.800
wǒ juéde zhège duì gāojí xuésheng jiūyīn
我觉得这个对高级学生纠音
I think correcting the pronunciation of advanced students.

00:16:20.800 --> 00:16:22.800
yīnggāi shì mànmàn lái de shì
应该是慢慢来的事
Should be a gradual process.

00:16:22.800 --> 00:16:23.666
bǐrúshuō
比如说
For example.

00:16:23.666 --> 00:16:25.400
rúguǒ shì yíge bānjí de xuésheng
如果是一个班级的学生
If it's a class of students.

00:16:25.433 --> 00:16:27.400
tāmen dōu yǒu fāyīn de wèntí dehuà
他们都有发音的问题的话
And they all have pronunciation issues.

00:16:27.400 --> 00:16:28.500
měicì shàngkè zhīqián
每次上课之前
Before every class.

00:16:28.500 --> 00:16:30.433
ràng tāmen měige rén dú yíge duǎnwén
让他们每个人读一个短文
Have each of them read a short passage.

00:16:30.433 --> 00:16:31.900
ràng tāmen zhège duǎnwén yìzhí liàn
让他们这个短文一直练
Have them practice this same passage repeatedly.

00:16:31.900 --> 00:16:34.133
bǐrú zhège xuéqī wǒmen jiù liàn zhè yíge duǎnwén
比如这个学期我们就练这一个短文
For example, we'll practice just this one passage for the whole semester.

00:16:34.133 --> 00:16:35.800
fāyīn duì le jiùxíng
发音对了就行
As long as the pronunciation is correct, it's fine.

00:16:35.800 --> 00:16:37.100
tā yìzhí liàn yìzhí liàn
他一直练一直练
They keep practicing and practicing.

00:16:37.100 --> 00:16:40.300
děng tā bǎ zhè yíge xiǎo duǎnwén dú de hěn biāozhǔn dehuà
等他把这一个小短文读的很标准的话
Once they can read this short passage very accurately.

00:16:40.300 --> 00:16:42.500
tā shuō biéde huà de shíhou
他说别的话的时候
When they say other things.

00:16:42.500 --> 00:16:44.100
tā yě huì zhīdào wèntí
他也会知道问题
They will also recognize the problems.

00:16:44.100 --> 00:16:45.466
tā zìjǐ jiù zhīdào wèntí le
他自己就知道问题了
They will notice the issues themselves.

00:16:45.466 --> 00:16:46.700
búyòng nǐ qù jiū(zhèng) tā
不用你去纠（正）他
You won't need to correct them.

00:16:46.766 --> 00:16:49.200
rúguǒ nǐ shì gāng kāishǐ xué fāyīn
如果你是刚开始学发音
If you are just starting to learn pronunciation.

00:16:49.233 --> 00:16:51.866
nà yídìng yào dǎhǎo yíge jīchǔ
那一定要打好一个基础
Then you must build a solid foundation.

00:16:51.866 --> 00:16:55.000
yīnwèi yídàn nǐ yǎngchéng le yíge xíguàn yǐhòu
因为一旦你养成了一个习惯以后
Because once you develop a habit.

00:16:55.000 --> 00:16:56.200
nǐ jiù gǎibuliǎo le
你就改不了了
You won't be able to change it.

00:16:56.200 --> 00:16:57.700
hěnnán hěnnán gǎi
很难很难改
It's very, very hard to fix.

00:16:57.700 --> 00:17:01.400
suǒyǐne rúguǒ nǐ xiànzài gāng kāishǐ xuéxí hànyǔ
所以呢 如果你现在刚开始学习汉语
So, if you are just starting to learn Chinese now.

00:17:01.400 --> 00:17:03.100
gāng kāishǐ xuéxí fāyīn
刚开始学习发音
Just starting to learn pronunciation.

00:17:03.100 --> 00:17:05.633
yídìng yào hǎohǎo de liànxí nǐde shēngdiào
一定要好好的练习 你的声调
You must practice your tones thoroughly.

00:17:05.633 --> 00:17:06.933
dǎhǎo yíge jīchǔ
打好一个基础
Build a good foundation.

00:17:06.933 --> 00:17:08.200
suǒyǐ zhè yào shuō dào tóu
所以这要说到头
So this brings us back to the root.

00:17:08.200 --> 00:17:09.466
shuō dào kāishǐ le
 说到开始了
Back to the very beginning.

00:17:09.500 --> 00:17:12.800
wǒ juéde tóngxué men yì kāishǐ xuéxí hànyǔ
我觉得同学们一开始学习汉语
I think when students first start learning Chinese.

00:17:12.800 --> 00:17:15.666
yídìng yào zhǎo yíge hěn zhuānyè de
一定要找一个很专业的
